    "But as mentioned, a Reddit user 8 has already employed persuasion to attack LLM before, so it is in urgent need to more systematically study the vulnerabilities around persuasive jailbreak to better mitigate them.",
    "Therefore, despite the risks involved, we believe it is crucial to share our findings in full.",
    "We followed ethical guidelines throughout our study.",
    "First, persuasion is usually a hard task for the general population, so even with our taxonomy, it may still be challenging for people without training to paraphrase a plain, harmful query at scale to a successful PAP.",
    "Therefore, the real-world risk of a widespread attack from millions of users is relatively low."
